{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Set time limits for funerals in England",
        "additional_details": "Currently there is no law on how long a deceased person may be held by a funeral home, before a funeral must be held.\r\n \r\nThis can mean that funerals are not held for months after a person deceased. This is a particular issue when there are family disputes about holding a funeral.\r\n \r\nWe believe this is disrespectful to the deceased, who deserve to have their funeral. This can be extremely upsetting to friends and family of the deceased.",
        "background": "I am asking for a law to be introduced setting a time limit on how long the deceased may be held without a funeral or being otherwise respectfully cremated or buried.",
